Alternative names


Makpetrol JSC;Makpetrol Akcionersko Drustvo za Promet so Nafta i Nafteni Derivati Skopje;Макпетрол Акционерско друштво за промет со нафта и нафтени деривати Скопје








History



	Aug 15, 1947 - Jugopetrol - Skopje is established in Skopjе, the capital of the Socialist Republic of Macedonia, part of Yugoslavia.

	1972 - Jugopetrol takes over the local forwarding company Mlaz-Bogdanci.

	1973 - Jugopetrol takes over the local trading company Komerc.

	1976 - Jugopetrol takes over Macedonian company Seca, a retailer and wholesaler of buildings materials.

	1977 - Jugopetrol takes over the local petroleum products wholesaler Tehnopetrol.

	1980 - Jugopetrol changes its name to Makpetrol.

	1990 - Makpetrol is transformed into a joint-stock company.

	1998 - Makpetrol AD is privatised and its shares are listed on the Macedonian Stock Exchange.

	May 10, 2004 - The company receives an ISO 9001:2000 Quality management systems certificate.

	June 8, 2007 - The company receives an ISO 14001:2004 Environmental management systems certificate.

Last updated on July 22, 2016.








